Sequence Information.Peptide Name: Defensin-TK (natural AMPs; frog, amphibians, animals; 3S=S; UCSS1a)
Sequence Information.Source: skin secretions, tree frog,Theloderma kwangsiensis, China, Asia

Literature Information.Literature: APD analysis reveals that the sequence of this peptide most resembles (81.8% similarity)PopuDef. Active against Gram+ S. aureus ATCC2592 (MIC 3 ug/ml), Gram- E .coli ATCC25922 (MIC 12 ug/ml), B. dysenteriae (MIC 3 ug/ml), and fungus C. albicans ATCC2002 (MIC 6 ug/ml). This peptide showed only low hemolyis (e.g., 6.2% at 200 ug/ml) of human red blood cells.
Literature Information.Author: Shen W, Chen Y, Yao H, Du C, Luan N, Yan X.2015
Literature Information.Title: A novel defensin-like antimicrobial peptide from the skin secretions of the tree frog, Theloderma kwangsiensis
